-Newtonian tidal precessions as large as $\\approx 1-10^2$ mas\nyr$^{-1}$ could be obtained, but the quite larger Newtonian tidal effects would\nbe a major source of systematic bias because of the present-day percent\nuncertainty in the product of the Earth's mass times the Newtonian\ngravitational parameter.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 10 Jun 2014 07:49:43 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 25 Jul 2014 07:04:21 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 31 Jul 2014 13:58:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-08-15"}
